-- Hasbro posts quarterly profit
-- 
-- Mon Apr 23, 2007 6:47am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/23/us-hasbro-results-idUSWNAS711420070423

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Hasbro Inc. HAS.N, the nation's second largest toy maker, on Monday posted a quarterly profit versus a year-earlier loss, helped by sales of board games and brands like Littlest Pet Shop and Playskool. 

 First-quarter net income totaled $32.9 million, or 19 cents a share, compared with a year-earlier loss of $4.9 million, or 3 cents a share.